Groups for the 2022 World Cup finals in Qatar following the draw on Friday: Group A: Qatar, Ecuador, Senegal, Netherlands Group B: England, Iran, USA, Wales or Scotland or Ukraine Group C: Argentina, Saudi Arabia, Mexico, Poland Group D: France, Peru or UAE or Australia, Denmark, Tunisia Group E: Spain, Costa Rica or New Zealand, Germany, Japan Group F: Belgium, Canada, Morocco, Croatia Group G: Brazil, Serbia, Switzerland, Cameroon Group H: Portugal, Ghana, Uruguay, South Korea — World Cup finals to be played from November 21 to December 18 — Intercontinental playoffs to be contested on June 13-14 in Qatar i) Winner of United Arab Emirates v Australia face Peru ii) New Zealand v Costa Rica — European playoffs to be held in June on dates to be announced